#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:19
msgid "CloseSpider"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:23
msgid ""
"This exception can be raised from a spider callback to request the spider to "
"be closed/stopped. Supported arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:26
msgid "the reason for closing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:29
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:31
msgid ""
"def parse_page(self, response):\n"
"    if \"Bandwidth exceeded\" in response.body:\n"
"        raise CloseSpider(\"bandwidth_exceeded\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:38
msgid "DontCloseSpider"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:42
msgid ""
"This exception can be raised in a :signal:`spider_idle` signal handler to "
"prevent the spider from being closed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:46
msgid "DropItem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:50
msgid ""
"The exception that must be raised by item pipeline stages to stop processing "
"an Item. For more information see :ref:`topics-item-pipeline`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:54
msgid "IgnoreRequest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:58
msgid ""
"This exception can be raised by the Scheduler or any downloader middleware "
"to indicate that the request should be ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:62
msgid "NotConfigured"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:66
msgid ""
"This exception can be raised by some components to indicate that they will "
"remain disabled. Those components include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:69
msgid "Extensions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:70
msgid "Item pipelines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:71
msgid "Downloader middlewares"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:72
msgid "Spider middlewares"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:74
msgid "The exception must be raised in the component's ``__init__`` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:77
msgid "NotSupported"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:81
msgid "This exception is raised to indicate an unsupported feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:84
msgid "StopDownload"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:88
msgid ""
"Raised from a :class:`~scrapy.signals.bytes_received` or :class:`~scrapy."
"signals.headers_received` signal handler to indicate that no further bytes "
"should be downloaded for a response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:91
msgid ""
"The ``fail`` boolean parameter controls which method will handle the "
"resulting response:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:94
msgid ""
"If ``fail=True`` (default), the request errback is called. The response "
"object is available as the ``response`` attribute of the ``StopDownload`` "
"exception, which is in turn stored as the ``value`` attribute of the "
"received :class:`~twisted.python.failure.Failure` object. This means that in "
"an errback defined as ``def errback(self, failure)``, the response can be "
"accessed though ``failure.value.response``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:101
msgid "If ``fail=False``, the request callback is called instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:103
msgid ""
"In both cases, the response could have its body truncated: the body contains "
"all bytes received up until the exception is raised, including the bytes "
"received in the signal handler that raises the exception. Also, the response "
"object is marked with ``\"download_stopped\"`` in its :attr:`~scrapy.http."
"Response.flags` attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:109
msgid ""
"``fail`` is a keyword-only parameter, i.e. raising ``StopDownload(False)`` "
"or ``StopDownload(True)`` will raise a :class:`TypeError`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exceptions.rst:113
msgid ""
"See the documentation for the :class:`~scrapy.signals.bytes_received` and :"
"class:`~scrapy.signals.headers_received` signals and the :ref:`topics-stop-"
"response-download` topic for additional information and examples."
msgstr ""
